                    "id": "combined_lifetime_vs_pathway1_rate",
                    "description": "Reproduces the `Effect of Multiple Removal Pathways` analysis from the GasChem.jl AtmosphericLifetime documentation. The first-order rate constant of pathway 1 is swept logarithmically over k_1 ∈ [1.0e-9, 1.0e-3] s⁻¹ while pathway 2 is held at its default k_2 = 2.0e-6 s⁻¹ (tau_2 = 5.0e5 s). As k_1 rises, pathway 1 becomes the faster sink: the combined lifetime tau_combined falls from the slow-k_1 plateau (≈ tau_2 = 5.0e5 s, pathway 2 limiting) through the equal-rate crossover toward the fast-k_1 asymptote tau_combined ≈ 1/k_1 = tau_1 (pathway 1 dominating). This is the Seinfeld & Pandis Ch. 2 result that the faster removal pathway controls the overall atmospheric lifetime.",
