                    "id": "combined_lifetime_regime_heatmap",
                    "description": "Combined atmospheric lifetime tau_combined as a joint function of the two pathway rate constants (2-D log-log sweep), k_1 ∈ [1.0e-8, 1.0e-4] s⁻¹ × k_2 ∈ [1.0e-8, 1.0e-4] s⁻¹. Because tau_combined = 1/(k_1 + k_2), the iso-lifetime contours are straight lines of constant k_1 + k_2: the long-lifetime corner (both rate constants small, slow removal) lies at lower-left and the short-lifetime corner (both large, fast removal) at upper-right. The surface also shows fast-pathway dominance — near either axis edge, whichever rate constant is larger sets tau_combined.",
